From c3fe8304d6981217f89f28cad315d1cfc486f9d5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Date: Thu, 4 Jun 2026 12:13:32 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] graphic_2d: fix RSWindowAnimationController crash when
 registered off the main runner
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

setController() from a launcher window's ArkUI thread (not the main event
runner) made the first controller callback SIGBUS in libace_napi. Three
distinct bugs, each surfacing only after the previous was fixed:

  1. Wrong thread. The On* callbacks arrive on a binder thread and were
     posted via an EventHandler bound to GetMainEventRunner(), but env_ and
     the JS controller live on the registering thread. Replace handler_ with
     PostTaskToJsThread(), which dispatches via napi_send_event(env_, ...) so
     the task always runs on env_'s own JS thread.

  2. No handle scope. napi_send_event invokes the task outside any native
     callback scope; the task creates napi values (CreateJsWindowAnimation*)
     and so dereferenced a null scope. Wrap the dispatched task in
     napi_open_handle_scope / napi_close_handle_scope.

  3. Double-deref in CallJsFunction. NativeReference::Get() already returns
     the referenced napi_value, but the code re-interpreted it as a napi_ref
     and called napi_get_reference_value() on it — dereferencing a value as a
     reference (the actual SIGBUS in native_api.cpp). Use Get() directly.

Also make jsController_ a per-instance member (was a namespace thread_local,
which only worked when SetJsController and the callback ran on the same
thread) and include napi/native_node_api.h for napi_send_event.

Change-Id: Id3861f4b7ce12e1cc647ae36d730ae12f43a9d55
Signed-off-by: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
